article.headline: Kennesaw 80, Jacksonville 76
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Andre Morgan scored 28 points as Kennesaw State rallied for an 80-76 win over Jacksonville in an Atlantic Sun Conference game on Sunday. The loss stretched Jacksonville's losing streak to 18 consecutive games, the longest current streak in the nation. Kennesaw State (12-12, 10-5) broke a four-game losing streak and moved to within a game of league-leader Lipscomb. Morgan hit 10 of 19 shots from the field, including a pair of three-pointers, and was perfect in six attempts from the foul line. Jacksonville (1-21, 1-14) held a 59-56 lead with 5:10 left in the game, Morgan scored 15 of Kennesaw State's next 17 points before fouling out with 23 seconds left in the game. Morgan's jumper at the 3:13 mark broke a 63-63 tie and gave the Owls the lead for good. He added a pair of three-point plays and another basket in the next two minutes to give Kennesaw a six-point lead. The Owls converted seven of eight shots from the free throw line in the last 29 seconds to secure the win. Antonio Cool scored 22 points to lead Jacksonville, but missed three free throws in the final 62 seconds of the game. Golden Ingle, the Owls' leading scorer at 17.6 points per game, missed the game due to an injured ankle suffered in Friday's loss at North Florida.
